[b]TVO - Big Ideas, October 15 2011: John Gray on The Immortalization Commission[/b]

Philosopher and author, John Gray, on [i]The Immortalization Commission: Science and the Strange Quest to Cheat Death[/i]. In the late nineteenth century and as a consequence of Darwinism, many thinkers turned to science to solve the riddle of death. Philosopher and author John Gray explores humankind's dangerous striving toward a scientific version of immortality.

